Comment: pndub_live said "[ heading home ]
- - - -
Well east coast, it's been real. It's been a pleasure spending time with family, exploring the brilliant place that is New York City, seeing old friends, and celebrating the holidays. Alas, all trips must end and so I will be just like many of the travelers in this photo; although I'll be taking to the air rather than the rails. The weirdest part about leaving the house you grew up in is not knowing when you'll be back next. Maybe it'll be a few months, maybe a year, maybe more. All in good time though.

As for New Years resolutions, I don't really do them. I strive to be the best I can be every single day. Why wait for the end of the year to become a better person? However one thing I have been trying to do as of late is actually to spend less time on social media. I used to be super active, particularly on Instagram, and it was just taking too much out of the time I could be enjoying the life right in front of me. I used to try to like all the photos of everyone I followed; and leave a comment on the large majority of them. Fact is, that's just insane. I love looking through all of you guys' amazing work. It's inspiring and gives me new ideas for places to visit, things to see, and characteristics I want to aspire to in myself. I guess you could say my one resolution is to live more authentically and less vicariously. So I'll leave it at this - want to get to know me more? Don't just double tap. I challenge you to make contact. I'm always available to chat, meet new people, and answer questions. With that said, have a safe, happy, and fulfilling new year."

Comment: emilygellis said "Wow! 2014 what a year you have been. I think I learned more lessons this year than I ever have before. The accomplishments I have achieved i still don't believe. The success of Emily Cho baffles me. You would not believe how the story started so small, and to think today it has the potential of being so big, it's unreal. The fact that another big company saw something in us, understood our vision is still amazing. I have watched three of my best friends get married this year, that's pretty crazy!! Time seriously flies, we were just sitting on the steps of our highschool eating bagel hut like yesterday. I was driving around in my car like I owned the world! Haha I didn't know shit at the time. Two most common questions of 2014 for me: 1. How did you do it? Sell your company? Well there is no manual, I worked my ass off and when I pitched to sell to my now partner, my passion was infectious because I really believed in what I was saying. I've done the research and I've watched it grow; I know the ins and outs and how to do better on the future. 2. How do you deal with your mom having Alzheimer's? This one is the most common and here's my answer. I didn't get a checklist asking how I wanted to have my parents age... These are my cards.... I don't know why but I don't have a choice, it is what it is. At the core my mom is the same person, I try and see her for that. It is extremely humbling to start to have to help your parent do things they did for you for your entire life. Trust me nobody is stronger than that woman, but she needs me, just like I needed her, and Ofcourse my number one priority of life before any success or even friendship will be making sure she is ok and happy. As long as queen Ô∏èE is happy, so am I. I feel very fortunate, but also I feel like my hardwork honestly paid off. So as I get a little older and wiser, and see some things maybe others find out a little later I will share some small insight.. Appreciate the little things. Respect your family, spend time with them, do shit that really makes you happy because that's all that matters. #cheers #love #2014 #igone #2015 #hifelicia"
